1: - [ ] Verify all functions have proper documentation\n492: - [ ] Verify all constants have proper documentation\n493: - [ ] Verify all exported types have proper documentation\n494: - [ ] Verify package-level documentation exists\n495: - [ ] Verify code follows Go best practices\n496: - [ ] Verify code follows project conventions\n497: \n498: **Verification**: Run final code review and verify all quality checks pass\n499: \n500: ---\n501: \n502: ## Summary\n503: \n504: **Total Tasks**: 40\n505: **Estimated Effort**: S (Small) - 6-8 hours\n506: \n507: ### Key Deliverables\n508: 1. **Agentd Controller** - Complete Kubernetes controller for idle cleanup\n509: 2. **Constants Definition** - Timeout and annotation key constants\n510: 3. **Reconcile Logic** - Core reconciliation logic with proper error handling\n511: 4. **SetupWithManager** - Controller registration with Kubernetes\n512: 5. **Main Entry Point** - Binary entry point with proper configuration\n513: 6. **Unit Tests** - Comprehensive unit tests for all scenarios\n514: 7. **Integration Tests** - End-to-end tests with real Kubernetes API\n515: 8. **RBAC Configuration** - ClusterRole and ServiceAccount manifests\n516: 9. **Deployment Manifest** - Kubernetes Deployment configuration\n517: 10. **Documentation** - README and inline documentation\n518: \n519: ### Success Criteria\n520: - All unit tests pass with >80% code coverage\n521: - Integration tests pass with envtest\n522: - Reconcile logic correctly handles all scenarios (not found, missing annotation, invalid annotation, not expired, expired)\n523: - Controller registers correctly with Kubernetes\n524: - Binary builds and runs without errors\n525: - RBAC permissions are correct and minimal\n526: - Deployment manifest follows Kubernetes best practices\n527: - Documentation is complete and accurate\n528: - Code passes static analysis and linting\n529: - Error handling is consistent and robust\n530: \n531: ### Dependencies\n532: - Go 1.24+\n533: - Kubernetes